# Server Actions & Data Validation

All data retrieval and mutations must use **Next.js Server Actions**. Never fetch data directly from client components.

## Server Actions

All database operations (select, insert, update, delete) must be performed inside server actions.

```ts
"use server";

import { db } from "@/db";
import { flashcardDecks } from "@/db/schema";
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";

export async function getDecks() {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthorized");

  return db.select().from(flashcardDecks).where(eq(flashcardDecks.userId, userId));
}
```

## Data Validation with Zod

All data passed into a server action **must** be validated with Zod before use.

```ts
// ❌ BAD — no validation, unsafe types
export async function createDeck(data: FormData) { ... }

// ✅ GOOD — typed input, validated with Zod
import { z } from "zod";

const CreateDeckSchema = z.object({
  title: z.string().min(1).max(100),
  description: z.string().optional(),
});

type CreateDeckInput = z.infer<typeof CreateDeckSchema>;

export async function createDeck(input: CreateDeckInput) {
  const parsed = CreateDeckSchema.parse(input);
  // use parsed.title, parsed.description safely
}
```

## Key Rules

- Always use `"use server"` at the top of server action files
- Never use `FormData` as a parameter type — use typed objects instead
- Define a Zod schema for every server action that accepts input
- Derive TypeScript types from Zod schemas using `z.infer<typeof Schema>`
- Call `schema.parse()` (throws on failure) or `schema.safeParse()` (returns result object) before accessing any input data
